main event: A bright, luminous object was observed moving from east to west over Chicago, Illinois on October 18, 1961.
interesting points: The object stopped and then accelerated at one point during the sighting.
The sighting was reported by military personnel from the 6LTH Troop Carrier Squadron at O'Hare International Airport.
The object was described as being very luminous and shaped, though no further details were provided.
The sighting lasted for an unspecified duration, but was reported to have occurred at 1637 hours.
The report was submitted to the Air Force Systems Command and Foreign Technology Division at Wright-Patterson AFB for further investigation.
witnesses: military personnel from the 6LTH Troop Carrier Squadron
